Subject: [PATCH 3/9] lsi/ncr: run ncr init earlier

The PCIe controller driver depends on ncr, so we
should init the ncr module before PCIe hcd.

Signed-off-by: Kevin Hao <kexin.hao@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/lsi/acp/ncr.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/lsi/acp/ncr.c b/drivers/lsi/acp/ncr.c
index ae48106..70f80e4 100644
--- a/drivers/lsi/acp/ncr.c
+++ b/drivers/lsi/acp/ncr.c
@@ -268,7 +268,7 @@ ncr_init( void )
 	return 0;
 }
 
-module_init( ncr_init );
+postcore_initcall(ncr_init );
 
